  <Subject Subject_ID="300042410">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300195685</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>double clarinets [300195685], reedpipes with single reed: with cylindrical bore [300195249], reedpipes with single reed [300205169], reedpipes (confined aerophones) [300042558], reeds (aerophones) [300193013], aerophones [300041622], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any of a group of pipes or sets of pipes, usually consisting of a single piece of wood with two narrow cylindrical bores each having an idioglot single reed, less often of two pipes inserted into a common stock which holds the reeds. Some terminate in bells or are attached to bags.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cualquiera de un grupo de tubos o juegos de tubos que generalmente consisten en una sola pieza de madera con dos orificios cilíndricos angostos, cada uno con una lengüeta idiofónica; menos frecuentemente consisten en dos tubos introducidos en una pieza común que lleva las lengüetas. Algunos terminan en campanas o están unidos a bolsas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sets pijpen, bestaande uit een enkel stuk hout met twee smalle cilindrische boringen, waarbij beide een idioglot enkel riet hebben. Soms met twee pijpen die in een gezamelijk blok zijn geplaatst, waarin de rieten zijn bevestigd. Sommige eindigen in een klankbeker of zitten vast aan luchtzakken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>多管樂器或成組的管樂器，通常由具兩個窄圓柱內管的單一木材構成，每個內管各具有一個自體單簧片，較罕見的情況是，兩個內管嵌入一個裝有簧片的柄。某些笛子的末端為號口，或連接一個風袋。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gruppe oder Satz von Pfeifen, jede gewöhnlich aus einem einzigen Holzstück mit zwei engen zylindrischen Bohrungen und einem idioglotten, einfachen Rohrblatt; seltener aus zwei Pfeifen, eingefügt in eine gemeinsame Halterung, die die Rohrblätter trägt. Einige Diple enden in einem Schalltrichter oder sind an Windsäcken angebracht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
